  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized cubes, then add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the potatoes are golden and crispy – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678800870620-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678800870620-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678800870620-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678800870620-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678800870620-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>diced chorizo</strong> to a pot over a medium-low heat and cook for 5-6 min or until the chorizo is crispy</p><p>While the chorizo is cooking, dice your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>black olives</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678800878568-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678800878568-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678800878568-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678800878568-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678800878568-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and add your<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once the chorizo is crispy, increase the heat to medium-high, then add the <strong>diced tomato</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!), <strong>tomato stock</strong>, a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-6 min or until the tomato has broken down and the sauce has reduced – this is your <strong>chorizo</strong> <strong>bravas sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678800886378-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678800886378-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678800886378-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678800886378-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678800886378-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chorizo bravas sauce is cooking, combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, the <strong>remaining grated garlic </strong>and a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>garlic & lemon</strong> <strong>aioli</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> and 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to a large bowl with your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add 90ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[135ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [180ml]</span> <strong>very cold water </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678800900731-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678800900731-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678800900731-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678800900731-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678800900731-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and cut in half on a diagonal</p><p>Sprinkle both sides of the<strong> basa</strong> with <strong>flour</strong> until fully coated, then tap off any excess</p><p>Dip the<strong> floured basa</strong> into the <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>batter</strong> and turn it several times until fully coated</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678800930453-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678800930453-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678800930453-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678800930453-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678800930453-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> (enough to coat the base of the pan) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min on each side until cooked through, golden and crispy – this is your <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>battered basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678800938761-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678800938761-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678800938761-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678800938761-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678800938761-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped olives</strong>,<strong> salad </strong>and <strong>sliced shallot </strong>in a large bowl with a squeeze of <strong>lemon </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>– this is your <strong>black olive salad</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678800948027-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678800948027-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678800948027-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678800948027-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678800948027-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>battered basa</strong> with the <strong>crispy potatoes</strong> and <strong>black olive salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the crispy<strong> </strong>potatoes with the <strong>chorizo</strong> <strong>bravas sauce</strong> – these are your <strong>chorizo</strong> <strong>patatas bravas</strong></p><p>Drizzle the<strong> garlic & lemon</strong> <strong>aioli</strong> all over the chorizo<strong> </strong>patatas bravas and garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
